cSctpExtMIB.name: cSctpExtMIB

revisions.description: Added support for effective destination address, count of fast retransmission per association and notification when destination address changes states. cSctpAssocExtEffectiveAddrType cSctpAssocExtEffectiveAddress cSctpAssocExtRtxChunksFast cSctpAddressStateNotifEnabled cSctpExtDestAddressStateChange cSctpAssocExtBundleFlag cSctpAssocExtBundleTimeout
MIB module developed for the SIGTRAN IETF group. Based on SCTP, RFC2960

cSctpExtMIB.contactinfo: Cisco Systems, Inc Customer Service Postal: 170 W. Tasman Drive San Jose, CA 95134 USA Tel: +1 800 553-NETS E-mail: cs-sctp@cisco.com
cSctpExtMIB.description: An extension to the CISCO-IETF-SCTP-MIB.my used to provide additional information to manage the Stream Control Transmission Protocol (RFC 2960).

cSctpStatRtxChucks.name: cSctpStatRtxChucks
cSctpStatRtxChucks.description: Number of SCTP chunks retransmitted due to the T3 timers expiring before the packet is acknowledged.

cSctpStatRtxChucksFast.name: cSctpStatRtxChucksFast
cSctpStatRtxChucksFast.reference: [sctp] section 7.2.4.- Fast Retransmit on Gap Reports.
cSctpStatRtxChucksFast.description: Number of SCTP chunks retransmitted using the fast-recovery retransmission mechanism specified in [sctp].

cSctpStatDestAddressFailures.name: cSctpStatDestAddressFailures
cSctpStatDestAddressFailures.description: The accumulated number of times a destination IP address was marked unavailable since the start of this association. The IP destination address will be marked unavailable when the specified number of retransmissions have failed.

cSctpCtrlPurgeTimeout.name: cSctpCtrlPurgeTimeout
cSctpCtrlPurgeTimeout.description: The amount of time the SCTP protocol software will wait before purging an associations TCB. An association TCB will exist until a management station sets the cSctpAssocState to deleteTCB or is purge by the protocol implementation. The protocol implementation will purge an association TCB using a combination of cSctpCtrlPurgeTimeout and cSctpCtrlMaxHeld. The cSctpCtrlPurgeTimeout ranges from the minimum of one hour to roughly one month. The default value is roughly one day.

cSctpCtrlMaxHeld.name: cSctpCtrlMaxHeld
cSctpCtrlMaxHeld.description: The maximum number of association TCBS that will be held after they have been marked closed and are no longer providing service. This limit is used to prevent excessive waste of resources.

cSctpAddressStateNotifEnabled.name: cSctpAddressStateNotifEnabled
cSctpAddressStateNotifEnabled.description: This object controls the generation of cSctpExtDestAddressStateChange as follows: 'true' Indicates that an address state change notification is to be generated whenever a IP address used by one or more associations becomes available or unavailable. That is, the notification generation is enabled. 'false' Indicates that an address state change notification generation is disabled.

cSctpAssocExtTable.name: cSctpAssocExtTable
cSctpAssocExtTable.description: A table containing SCTP association-specific information.

cSctpAssocExtEntry.name: cSctpAssocExtEntry
cSctpAssocExtEntry.description: General common variables and statistics for the whole association.

cSctpAssocExtRtoMin.name: cSctpAssocExtRtoMin
cSctpAssocExtRtoMin.reference: [SIGAS] Telephony Signaling Transport over SCTP Applicability Statement
cSctpAssocExtRtoMin.description: The minimum value permitted by a SCTP implementation for the retransmission timeout, measured in milliseconds. More refined semantics for objects of this type depend upon the algorithm used to determine the retransmission timeout. Minimum recommended value is 1000 milliseconds. Some telephony applications could require less than 1 second, see [SIGAS] for further information.

cSctpAssocExtRtoMax.name: cSctpAssocExtRtoMax
cSctpAssocExtRtoMax.description: The maximum value permitted by a SCTP implementation for the retransmission timeout, measured in milliseconds. More refined semantics for objects of this type depend upon the algorithm used to determine the retransmission timeout. Recommended value is 60000 milliseconds.

cSctpAssocExtRtoInitial.name: cSctpAssocExtRtoInitial
cSctpAssocExtRtoInitial.description: Initial value for the Retransmission timer. Recommended value is 3000 milliseconds.

cSctpAssocExtValCookieLife.name: cSctpAssocExtValCookieLife
cSctpAssocExtValCookieLife.description: Valid cookie life in the 4-way start-up handshake procedure. Recommended value: 60000 milliseconds.

cSctpAssocExtMaxInitRetr.name: cSctpAssocExtMaxInitRetr
cSctpAssocExtMaxInitRetr.description: The maximum number of retransmissions at the start-up phase (INIT and COOKIE ECHO chunks). Recommended value: 8 attempts.

cSctpAssocExtMTU.name: cSctpAssocExtMTU
cSctpAssocExtMTU.description: The Maximum Transmission Size to be used by this association. The size will the smallest MTU size supported by any of the IP Addresses used by the association.

cSctpAssocExtLocRecWnd.name: cSctpAssocExtLocRecWnd
cSctpAssocExtLocRecWnd.description: The current local receive window size for this association.

cSctpAssocExtLocRecWndLowMark.name: cSctpAssocExtLocRecWndLowMark
cSctpAssocExtLocRecWndLowMark.description: Low water mark for Local Receive Window Size.

cSctpAssocExtLocRecWndZeroCnt.name: cSctpAssocExtLocRecWndZeroCnt
cSctpAssocExtLocRecWndZeroCnt.description: Number of times the Local Receive window reached zero bytes.

cSctpAssocExtRemRecWnd.name: cSctpAssocExtRemRecWnd
cSctpAssocExtRemRecWnd.description: The Remote Receive Window Size for this association.

cSctpAssocExtRemRecWndLowMark.name: cSctpAssocExtRemRecWndLowMark
cSctpAssocExtRemRecWndLowMark.description: Low water mark for Remote Receive Window Size.

cSctpAssocExtRemRecWndZeroCnt.name: cSctpAssocExtRemRecWndZeroCnt
cSctpAssocExtRemRecWndZeroCnt.description: Number of times the Remote Receive window reached zero bytes.

cSctpAssocExtUlpQueued.name: cSctpAssocExtUlpQueued
cSctpAssocExtUlpQueued.description: Current number of IP datagrams waiting to be sent.

cSctpAssocExtUlpQueuedHW.name: cSctpAssocExtUlpQueuedHW
cSctpAssocExtUlpQueuedHW.description: High water mark for data grams waiting to be sent. Resetting this object is achieved by setting this object to 0. Attempting to set this object to any other value will result in a wrongValue error.

cSctpAssocExtUlpQueuedRT.name: cSctpAssocExtUlpQueuedRT
cSctpAssocExtUlpQueuedRT.description: The time when cSctpAssocUlpQueuedHW was set to 0.

cSctpAssocExtChunksRecControl.name: cSctpAssocExtChunksRecControl
cSctpAssocExtChunksRecControl.description: Number of control Chucks received by this association.

cSctpAssocExtChunksRecOrdered.name: cSctpAssocExtChunksRecOrdered
cSctpAssocExtChunksRecOrdered.description: Number of Chucks received by this association where order is required.

cSctpAssocExtChunksRecUnOrdered.name: cSctpAssocExtChunksRecUnOrdered
cSctpAssocExtChunksRecUnOrdered.description: Number of Chucks received by this association where order is not required.

cSctpAssocExtChunksSentControl.name: cSctpAssocExtChunksSentControl
cSctpAssocExtChunksSentControl.description: Number of control Chucks sent by this association.

cSctpAssocExtChunksSentOrdered.name: cSctpAssocExtChunksSentOrdered
cSctpAssocExtChunksSentOrdered.description: Number of Chucks sent by this association where order is required.

cSctpAssocExtChunksSentUnOrdered.name: cSctpAssocExtChunksSentUnOrdered
cSctpAssocExtChunksSentUnOrdered.description: Number of Chucks sent by this association where order is not required.

cSctpAssocExtDatagramsRec.name: cSctpAssocExtDatagramsRec
cSctpAssocExtDatagramsRec.description: Number of IP datagrams received by this association.

cSctpAssocExtDatagramsSent.name: cSctpAssocExtDatagramsSent
cSctpAssocExtDatagramsSent.description: Number of IP datagrams sent by this association.

cSctpAssocExtEffectiveAddrType.name: cSctpAssocExtEffectiveAddrType
cSctpAssocExtEffectiveAddrType.description: Internet type of effective destination IP address. This is the type of IP address to which traffic is currently sent for this association.

cSctpAssocExtEffectiveAddress.name: cSctpAssocExtEffectiveAddress
cSctpAssocExtEffectiveAddress.description: Effective destination IP address. This is the IP address to which traffic is currently sent for this association. This value can be any of the IP addresses defined in the cSctpAssocRemAddressExtTable Table.

cSctpAssocExtRtxChunksFast.name: cSctpAssocExtRtxChunksFast
cSctpAssocExtRtxChunksFast.reference: RFC 2960 section 7.2.4. - Fast Retransmit on Gap Reports.
cSctpAssocExtRtxChunksFast.description: The accumulated number of SCTP chunks retransmitted using the fast-recovery retransmission mechanism specified in [sctp] since the start of this association.

cSctpAssocExtBundleFlag.name: cSctpAssocExtBundleFlag
cSctpAssocExtBundleFlag.description: This objects indicates if the SCTP protocol allows chunks to be bundled into a single datagram as follows: 'true(1)' Indicates that chunks will be bundled. 'false(2)' Indicates that chunks will not be bundled.

cSctpAssocExtBundleTimeout.name: cSctpAssocExtBundleTimeout
cSctpAssocExtBundleTimeout.description: The amount time to wait to allow data chunks to accumulate so that they can be transmitted in the same datagram. The arrival of the first data chunk will start a timer that will expire in the specified milliseconds. All later chunks will be delayed until the timer expires. When the timer expires the data chunks will be sent out in one or more datagrams.

cSctpAssocRemAddressExtTable.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressExtTable
cSctpAssocRemAddressExtTable.description: Expanded table of cSctpAssocRemAddressExtTable based on the AssocId index.

cSctpAssocRemAddressExtEntry.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressExtEntry
cSctpAssocRemAddressExtEntry.description: Additional information about destination IP addresses.

cSctpAssocRemAddressFailedCnt.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressFailedCnt
cSctpAssocRemAddressFailedCnt.description: Number of times the destination address was marked as failed.

cSctpAssocRemAddressSRTT.name: cSctpAssocRemAddressSRTT
cSctpAssocRemAddressSRTT.description: The Smoothed Round Trip Time(SRTT) is obtained by averaging the measured Rount trip times(RTT) between the local and remote systems on an IP Network. A value of '0' is reported for SRTT prior to the first successful RTT calculation.

cSctpExtDestAddressStateChange.name: cSctpExtDestAddressStateChange
cSctpExtDestAddressStateChange.description: The notification is generated when the state transition of cSctpAssocRemAddressStatus has occurred.

cSctpExtStatGroup.name: cSctpExtStatGroup
cSctpExtStatGroup.description: A collection of objects providing SCTP per system basis statistics for all associations.

cSctpExtCtrlGroup.name: cSctpExtCtrlGroup
cSctpExtCtrlGroup.description: A collection of objects providing SCTP per system basis control behavior for all associations.

cSctpExtAssocCtrlGroup.name: cSctpExtAssocCtrlGroup
cSctpExtAssocCtrlGroup.description: Objects used to control the behavior each association.

cSctpExtAssocStatGroup.name: cSctpExtAssocStatGroup
cSctpExtAssocStatGroup.description: Objects used to collect information and statistics on each association.

cSctpExtAssocRemAddrGroup.name: cSctpExtAssocRemAddrGroup
cSctpExtAssocRemAddrGroup.description: Objects used to collect information and statistics on each destination IP address.

cSctpExtAssocNotificationsGroup.name: cSctpExtAssocNotificationsGroup
cSctpExtAssocNotificationsGroup.description: Object used to provide notifications of state changes on destination IP addresses.

cSctpExtCtrlGroupRev1.name: cSctpExtCtrlGroupRev1
cSctpExtCtrlGroupRev1.description: A collection of objects providing SCTP per system basis control behavior for all associations.

cSctpExtAssocStatGroupRev1.name: cSctpExtAssocStatGroupRev1
cSctpExtAssocStatGroupRev1.description: Objects used to collect information and statistics on each association.
